---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME, SITE_URL } from '../lib/constants';

const title = 'Privacy Policy — Your Data Rights and Our Practices';
const description = `${SITE_NAME} privacy policy. Learn how we protect your data, your CCPA and GDPR rights, and our commitment to cookie-less, privacy-first analytics.`;
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} noIndex={true}>
  <section class="px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 2026</p>

      <h2>1. Overview</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE_NAME} ({SITE_URL}) is committed to protecting your privacy. This privacy policy explains how
        we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our website and calculators, in compliance
        with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), the California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA), and
        other applicable privacy laws.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Data Controller</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Controller:</strong> Mottalib Radif</li>
        <li><strong>Website:</strong> {SITE_URL}</li>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@truetakehomepay.com">contact@truetakehomepay.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>Calculator Inputs</h3>
      <p>
        All calculations are performed entirely in your browser using client-side JavaScript. Your salary,
        tax, and financial information <strong>never leaves your device</strong>. We do not collect, store,
        or transmit any calculator inputs to our servers. The technical architecture is designed according
        to the principle of "privacy by design".
      </p>
      <p>
        For clarity, the website does not collect or process: salary or income data, Social Security numbers,
        tax filing information, bank account details, or any other personal financial information entered
        into the calculators.
      </p>

      <h3>Analytics</h3>
      <p>
        We use <a href="https://plausible.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Plausible Analytics</a>,
        a privacy-focused, cookie-less analytics service. Plausible does not use cookies, does not collect
        personal data, does not store IP addresses, does not use fingerprinting, and is fully compliant with
        GDPR, CCPA, and PECR. We collect only aggregate data such as page views, referral sources, device
        types, and general geographic regions (country-level).
      </p>
      <p>
        Plausible processes all data on servers within the European Union. No individual visitors can be
        identified from the collected data. For more information:
        <a href="https://plausible.io/data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://plausible.io/data-policy</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>URL Parameters</h3>
      <p>
        When you use our calculators, your inputs may be encoded in the page URL (e.g., ?gross=60000&state=CA)
        to enable sharing. This data exists only in your browser's address bar and is not transmitted to or
        stored on our servers.
      </p>

      <h3>Server Log Files</h3>
      <p>
        Our hosting provider (Vercel) may automatically collect standard server log files including browser
        type, operating system, referrer URL, hostname, time of request, and IP address (anonymised). This
        data is used for security purposes and automatically deleted. It is not merged with other data
        sources.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        {SITE_NAME} does not use tracking cookies. No advertising, profiling, or third-party cookies are
        placed. The only data stored in your browser is your dark mode preference (via localStorage), which
        is not a cookie and is not transmitted to any server.
      </p>
      <p>
        localStorage is a local storage mechanism provided by the HTML5 standard. Data stored in localStorage
        remains on your device and is never sent to external servers. You can clear localStorage data at any
        time through your browser settings. Since no tracking cookies are used, a cookie consent banner is
        not legally required.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        This website is hosted on Vercel. Vercel may collect minimal technical data as part of their edge
        network service. See <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vercel's privacy policy</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may load web fonts from third-party content delivery networks for uniform text display. These
        services may receive your IP address as part of the standard HTTP request. This usage is based on
        our legitimate interest in a uniform presentation.
      </p>
      <p>
        We do not integrate any third-party services that profile users. There are no social media buttons,
        advertising widgets, remarketing services, or other tools that allow third parties to track users.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your Rights Under CCPA (California Residents)</h2>
      <p>If you are a California resident, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Know what personal information we collect about you</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your personal information</li>
        <li>Opt out of the sale of your personal information (we do not sell personal data)</li>
        <li>Not be discriminated against for exercising your privacy rights</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Since we do not collect personal information through our calculators, these rights are effectively
        exercised by default. We do not sell, trade, or transfer personal data to third parties.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Your Rights Under GDPR (EU Users)</h2>
      <p>
        Under the General Data Protection Regulation, EU users have the following rights:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Right of access</strong> (Art. 15): obtain confirmation of whether personal data is being processed.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to rectification</strong> (Art. 16): obtain correction of inaccurate data.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to erasure</strong> (Art. 17): obtain deletion of personal data.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to restriction</strong> (Art. 18): restrict processing in certain cases.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to portability</strong> (Art. 20): receive data in a machine-readable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to object</strong> (Art. 21): object to processing on grounds relating to your situation.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to withdraw consent</strong> (Art. 7): withdraw consent at any time.</li>
        <li><strong>Right to lodge a complaint</strong> (Art. 77): lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Since no personal data is collected, these rights are currently not applicable in practice. For
        any enquiry, contact us at contact@truetakehomepay.com. We undertake to respond within 30 days.
      </p>

      <h2>8. State Privacy Laws</h2>
      <p>
        We comply with applicable state privacy laws including the Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act
        (VCDPA), Colorado Privacy Act (CPA), Connecticut Data Privacy Act (CTDPA), and Utah Consumer
        Privacy Act (UCPA).
      </p>

      <h2>9. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our website is not directed to children under 13 and we do not knowingly collect personal
        information from children in compliance with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).
      </p>

      <h2>10. Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        Our website is served over a secure HTTPS connection that encrypts all data in transit. Appropriate
        technical and organizational measures are implemented to ensure a level of security appropriate to
        the risk.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or
        applicable law. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. The current
        version is always available on this page.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights, contact us at:<br />
        <a href="mailto:contact@truetakehomepay.com">contact@truetakehomepay.com</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
